{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if you had gone on the street, which was not safe to do, we could've actually seen the synagogue burning.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My particular synagogue, yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "People did tend to stay close to their own temples or synagogues because it wasn't customary in those days to own cars and automobiles, like we know in the United States.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were Reform Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We kept a very strict household, not kosher, but religious holidays, and we went to temple on Friday nights, sometimes on Saturday mornings.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Obviously, at that time, I was not 13 years old.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I had anticipated my bar mitzvah sometime down the road.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so it became a very comfortable and I would say routine activity for us to attend Friday night synagogue, yes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was the synagogue, the largest in Cologne.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They had some smaller ones, but this was a very, very major structure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And obviously, all of the synagogues in major cities had been destroyed that particular evening.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, my-- I only had one grandmother on my father's side.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She lived in Bad Godesberg.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Bad Godesberg, unfortunately, was Hitler's favorite retreat for a vacation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my family had lived there for over 180 years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were a very prominent family, having grown up for such a long time in one community.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My other parents were-- well, he was a little winemaker, as we would say, and he lived in Bad Kreuznach.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now interestingly enough, cities with a B-A-D in front of it means it's usually a resort, a recreational city, built up for various reasons, baths and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so they were very popular cities in which it was actually quite favorable for Jews to live and to thrive before 1933.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But that is the-- the family background on my grandparents' side.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
